1
00:00:21,061 --> 00:00:23,271
<i>Previously, on Battlestar Galactica</i>

2
00:00:23,439 --> 00:00:25,095
I'm promoting you to Captain.

3
00:00:25,328 --> 00:00:27,194
I'm making you commander
of the Pegasus Air Group.

4
00:00:27,234 --> 00:00:28,539
You're promoting me ?

5
00:00:29,018 --> 00:00:30,615
I need a CAG with guts.

6
00:00:30,854 --> 00:00:32,787
We are the leaders of this fleet.

7
00:00:33,094 --> 00:00:35,012
As such, we need to set an example.

8
00:00:35,206 --> 00:00:38,271
Oh, let's just cut through
the handholding, shall we ?

9
00:00:38,337 --> 00:00:40,976
Two of his men murdered one of my officers,

10
00:00:41,276 --> 00:00:43,134
while protecting a Cylon.

11
00:00:43,437 --> 00:00:45,647
They're guilty, they admitted it.

12
00:00:45,938 --> 00:00:48,762
And under regulations,
I have complete authority

13
00:00:48,934 --> 00:00:50,788
to try, convict, and sentence them.

14
00:00:50,929 --> 00:00:54,516
And you and I both know that the
penalty for that crime is death.

15
00:00:55,290 --> 00:00:58,980
I'm afraid there is only one end to this.
We've got to kill her.

16
00:01:00,661 --> 00:01:02,612
Well, I see that you got it to eat.

17
00:01:02,994 --> 00:01:04,753
That's progress, I suppose.

18
00:01:05,034 --> 00:01:08,586
Can you get it to roll over... beg ?

19
00:01:11,687 --> 00:01:13,002
Admiral, please !

20
00:01:13,794 --> 00:01:16,130
I thought you might like
a fresh set of clothes.

21
00:01:18,643 --> 00:01:19,920
You know what I miss ?

22
00:01:20,258 --> 00:01:21,232
Sports.

23
00:01:21,532 --> 00:01:24,138
I used to go the pyramid court
just before game time.

24
00:01:24,556 --> 00:01:25,983
Scalp two tickets.

25
00:01:26,133 --> 00:01:27,467
One for me, and one for you.

26
00:01:27,730 --> 00:01:29,824
I always liked to feel
that you were there with me.

27
00:01:31,998 --> 00:01:34,890
The Cylons call this
their Resurrection ship.

28
00:01:35,190 --> 00:01:37,813
At the moment, we are too far away
from the cylon home world

29
00:01:37,970 --> 00:01:41,278
for the normal downloading process to work,
which is why they built this ship.

30
00:01:41,719 --> 00:01:45,278
It contains the entire apparatus
necessary for Cylon resurrection.

31
00:01:45,456 --> 00:01:48,067
Then any Cylon who dies out here...

32
00:01:48,142 --> 00:01:49,475
Would be dead.

33
00:01:49,907 --> 00:01:51,763
As in, really dead.

34
00:01:52,036 --> 00:01:54,862
Our primary objective is a
Cylon vessel called Resurrection

35
00:01:54,946 --> 00:01:58,064
Our plan is to jump in
in the Blackbird stealth fighter

36
00:01:58,430 --> 00:02:00,995
and take out the FTL drives
on the Resurrection ship,

37
00:02:01,043 --> 00:02:02,428
preventing it from jumping away.

38
00:02:02,479 --> 00:02:03,845
When the FTL is destroyed,

39
00:02:03,883 --> 00:02:06,911
our attack squadrons will go
after the resurrection ship itself.

40
00:02:07,090 --> 00:02:08,179
How many squadrons ?

41
00:02:10,141 --> 00:02:11,195
All of'em.

42
00:02:12,677 --> 00:02:16,320
Jack, I want to transfer a detachment
of marines to Galactica.

43
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:18,319
I have a mission for you, Kara.

44
00:02:18,391 --> 00:02:19,818
Anything for you, you know that.

45
00:02:20,015 --> 00:02:22,645
Position marines in key areas
throughout the ship...

46
00:02:22,710 --> 00:02:25,587
I will ask for you over the wireless.

47
00:02:25,681 --> 00:02:28,375
I will call you directly, and
when I have you on the line

48
00:02:28,460 --> 00:02:31,906
and you hear me give
the command "execute case orange"

49
00:02:32,122 --> 00:02:35,646
You are to terminate Adama's command.
Started with Adama.

50
00:02:35,749 --> 00:02:37,433
I want you to pull out your weapon

51
00:02:38,407 --> 00:02:40,755
and shoot Admiral Cain in the head.

52
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:09,333
48 HOURS EARLIER

53
00:04:10,873 --> 00:04:12,547
This is a fracked-up thing

54
00:04:12,667 --> 00:04:14,038
that I've been asked to do.

55
00:04:15,362 --> 00:04:16,930
But we kill people for a living.

56
00:04:17,766 --> 00:04:19,456
They say shoot, we shoot.

57
00:04:20,831 --> 00:04:22,643
So you're gonna do this ?

58
00:04:25,579 --> 00:04:27,098
Yeah, I'm gonna do it.

59
00:04:29,091 --> 00:04:30,208
Kara.

60
00:04:30,622 --> 00:04:31,945
I could use some backup.

61
00:04:33,394 --> 00:04:34,941
I'll understand if you can't.

62
00:04:39,245 --> 00:04:40,691
You know better than that.

63
00:04:43,285 --> 00:04:44,645
Yeah, I guess so.

64
00:04:52,359 --> 00:04:54,153
People have to have this, Kara.

65
00:04:55,883 --> 00:04:57,019
Trust.

66
00:04:58,363 --> 00:04:59,637
Your word

67
00:05:00,109 --> 00:05:01,273
and my word.

68
00:05:03,790 --> 00:05:05,399
We don't have this, then...

69
00:05:07,170 --> 00:05:09,273
we really are no different than the Cylons.

70
00:05:16,145 --> 00:05:17,605
Thank you.

71
00:05:37,362 --> 00:05:38,821
Oh, looky here.

72
00:05:44,711 --> 00:05:46,358
Sunshine boys are here.

73
00:05:50,322 --> 00:05:54,153
You know, the man you killed saved
my life and the lives of 50 other men,

74
00:05:54,256 --> 00:05:55,351
you miserable frack.

75
00:05:57,006 --> 00:05:58,062
You,

76
00:05:58,647 --> 00:06:00,102
You call me "sir".

77
00:06:01,455 --> 00:06:02,450
Yes, sir.

78
00:06:02,591 --> 00:06:06,394
So I guess you were both getting your poles
greased by that filthy little robot girl ?

79
00:06:08,518 --> 00:06:11,502
I'm sorry. I don't think
I quite heard that right.

80
00:06:13,381 --> 00:06:15,957
The glass. I can't hear you.

81
00:06:16,930 --> 00:06:19,925
So, why don't you open the door, come in,

82
00:06:21,193 --> 00:06:23,052
and we'll talk about it in here.

83
00:06:25,638 --> 00:06:27,006
That's a great idea, Chief.

84
00:06:28,125 --> 00:06:29,433
They really want to do things.

85
00:06:29,608 --> 00:06:31,143
Hands over your head.

86
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:34,714
- Hey, hey, hey, slow down !
- On your knees, on your fracking knees !

87
00:06:35,585 --> 00:06:36,648
Slow it down, slow it down

88
00:06:36,761 --> 00:06:38,230
Just think about what you're doing here.

89
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:40,216
Just think about what we're doing here, guys.

90
00:06:40,294 --> 00:06:41,487
What the frack is this ?

91
00:06:41,618 --> 00:06:42,905
Don't worry, sir.

92
00:06:43,130 --> 00:06:45,515
We'll take it real slow, Sir !

